## Strengths
| ✅ | What works well |
|---|-----------------|
| **Clear project purpose** – The overview immediately tells the reader that the repo is a collection of Fortran MPI/OpenMP demos. |
| **Feature list** – The “Key Features” section concisely enumerates the main scientific/parallel‑computing concepts covered. |
| **Comprehensive file inventory** – Both *Folder Structure* and *Important Files* list every source file, making it easy to locate a program of interest. |
| **High‑level description of paradigms** – The “How it Works” section explains the difference between the MPI and OpenMP examples and mentions the Monte‑Carlo and CO₂ distance calculations. |
| **Future‑oriented suggestions** – The “Improvements” bullet list already points out useful next steps (testing, documentation, visualization, etc.). |

